<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 92 / International Company News: Hopewell raises HKDollars 2bn
for Chinese development
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
HOPEWELL Holdings, the Hong Kong-based property development and construction
company, has raised HKDollars 2bn (USDollars 259m) from a private placement
to fund a toll bridge and property developments connected to its 304km
super-highway in China.
The company issued 400m new shares at HKDollars 5 each, representing 9 per
cent of its enlarged share capital. Response was enthusiastic, reflecting
demand from international institutions for China 'plays'.
Hopewell's shares have been the best performing among the Hang Seng Index
constituents this year. Although it had a net cash position of about Dollars
HK4bn, it is undertaking several ambitious projects throughout the region,
including the Guangzhou-Shenzhen toll road project in China, its HKDollars
25bn Bangkok mass transit system and power stations in China, the
Philippines and Malaysia.
The latest China property developments are all linked to the company's
super-highway. Hopewell plans to develop a 3.12m sq ft site adjacent to the
toll road's border crossing with Hong Kong at a cost of HKDollars 300m.
A further 7.75m sq ft of retail and commercial space will be developed on 12
intersections of the super-highway, taking up HKDollars 1.15bn of the new
capital.
</TEXT>
