<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 92 / Lex to buy Swan National retail arm
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN DONE, Motor Industry Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LEX SERVICE, a leading UK motor retailer, is to acquire the Swan National
motor group, the UK's 11th largest dealership concern, in a deal worth
around Pounds 46m.
Swan National motor group, the retail motor distribution arm of Swan
National, a wholly-owned subsidiary of the TSB banking group, has 23 UK
dealerships.
The deal will make Lex the second-largest publicly quoted car retail group
in the UK with 86 dealerships.
The planned acquisition is the latest move in a radical restructuring of UK
motor retailing. Late last year Inchcape, the international motor
distribution and motor retailing group, took over Tozer Kemsley &amp; Millbourn
(TKM) making Inchcape one of the world's biggest independent car
distribution and retailing groups.
At the same time, the privately-owned AFG motor dealer group, controlled by
Mr Octav Botnar, reduced its 160-strong dealer network to 127 and aims to
retain more than 100 dealerships with a range of franchises.
Lex Service's planned takeover of Swan National motor group follows its
expected loss of the exclusive UK importer/distributorship for Volvo in the
UK.
Lex said the Swan National deal was conditional on the Volvo transaction,
worth a net Pounds 77m to Lex, being approved by its shareholders and given
clearance by the European Commission competition authorities.
Under the deal Lex will acquire the Swan National dealerships for Pounds 26m
in cash and repay inter-company loans of about Pounds 20m.
Swan National sold about 18,500 new vehicles in the year to the end of
September. It holds dealer franchises for Ford (4), Vauxhall (6), Peugeot
(3), Mercedes-Benz (3), and Rover (2) as well as single outlets for Fiat,
Jaguar, Land Rover, Renault and Volvo.
The acquisition of the Swan National operations would raise its share of the
UK new car market from 1.7 per cent to 2.6 per cent.
The existing Lex Retail group has a turnover of Pounds 594m, 3,600
employees, 57 dealerships and a sales volume of 27,000 new and 17,000 used
cars. Swan National has a turnover of Pounds 309m, 1,200 employees, 23
dealerships and a sales volume of 18,500 new cars and 7,400 used cars.
</TEXT>
