<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 92 / Letter: Search for a new job
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr DUNCAN I BROWN and Ms FIONA L BELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Michael Dixon (Recruitment, April 29) considered why a recent opinion
survey carried out by the Wyatt Company showed a significant increase in the
proportion of employees intending to find a new job now in comparison with a
similar survey in 1988.
However, the conclusion that there is an increase in employees with 'itchy
feet', dissatisfied with their current jobs is not the only explanation
which can be drawn. Rather, it may be that in a more buoyant job market four
years ago, more employees thinking about a move could actually do so and
therefore fall out of the statistics. Nowadays, with continuing high
employment, many of those wanting a move for positive or negative reasons
can only stay put, waiting for a suitable opportunity - filling surveys
while they wait.
Duncan I Brown,
Fiona L Bell,
41 Copthall Gardens,
Twickenham TW1 4HH
</TEXT>
