FT  07 MAY 92 / Recovery in US uneven
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE US economy is picking up but the recovery is uneven, the Federal Reserve
said yesterday, Reuter reports from Washington.
The latest Beige Book survey of economic conditions by the Fed's 12 district
banks gave a guarded assessment of the economy. The report said
manufacturing had picked up in most parts of the country, along with home
construction, although the rate of building appeared to have slowed.
Many districts had reported gains in retail sales and more optimism among
retailers about future sales. Loan demand was beginning to increase, but it
remained uneven. Most banks across the country reported an increase in
mortgage originations and a slowdown in refinancings. Demand for
non-mortgage loans was soft.
On inflation, the report said producer and consumer prices were generally
stable.
