FT  06 MAY 92 / ABB wins turboset contract
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Asea Brown Boveri, the Swedish-Swiss engineering group, announced yesterday
that it had secured a Dollars 210m contract from the German company VEAG to
design and supply two turbosets with a total output of 1,600MW for a power
plant to be built at Boxberg in Saxony, writes Robert Taylor in Stockholm.
The first turboset is scheduled to supply electricity from mid-1996 and the
second from six months later. The order for ABB follows one worth Dollars
50m a few weeks ago for the same Saxon plant. The contract will be carried
out with ABB Bergman Borsig of Berlin.
