<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Russia plans to trade machinery, aircraft and factory equipment for Chinese
food and consumer goods under a pact on economic ties signed in Beijing
yesterday, Reuter reports from Moscow. The protocol, according to the
Itar-Tass news agency, specified the volume of goods that the two will
supply to each other through direct trade, local deals over the border,
barter and exchange agreements and other means.
