<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAY 92 / BT and Visa agreement
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HOLDERS of Visa credit and debit cards will soon be able to pay for domestic
and international telephone calls on their card account under a deal between
British Telecom and Visa International.
VisaPhone, which is already available in the US, allows callers to provide
their card number and an identification number to pay for calls. The system
will be fully introduced in the UK early next year.
Visitors to the UK will be able to bill calls to their Visa card in local
currency. UK banks which issue Visa cards are expected to offer the service
in the next few months.
</TEXT>
