FT  06 MAY 92 / Gold reserves rise by Dollars 63m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITAIN'S gold and foreign currency reserves rose by an underlying Dollars
63m last month, the Treasury said yesterday. The overall level - which
includes cash gained from sales of Ecu-denominated Treasury bills and other
changes  - rose by Dollars 748m to reach Dollars 45.8bn on April 30.
