FT  06 MAY 92 / Car deal will create 500 jobs in Wales
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GRIFFITHS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NEARLY 500 jobs are to be created in West Glamorgan, south Wales, as a
result of a contract to supply wiring systems to Japanese car plants in the
UK, John Griffiths writes.
The contract  - the second won by the joint venture company between Lucas
and Sumitomo Electrical Industries of Japan  - is worth Pounds 20m a year.
Lucas SEI Wiring Systems' plant at Ystradgynlais will supply Honda's
manufacturing plant at Swindon, Wiltshire, due to go on stream in the
autumn.
