<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAY 92 / Boutros Ghali warns on troop deployment delays in Cambodia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL LITTLEJOHNS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Delays in the UN's troop deployment in Cambodia could have a negative effect
on its peace-keeping operation unless they were soon remedied, Mr Boutros
Boutros Ghali, secretary-general, warned last night, writes Michael
Littlejohns.
In a report to the Security Council, he mentioned the slow pace of
recruiting and deploying civilian administrators, which could impair the
UN's ability to maintan supervision and control.
