<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAY 92 / Observer: Not so chummy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
At first sight the battle for Midland Bank seems to be getting ever so cosy.
Lloyds Bank has hired GJW to do its political lobbying, while its rival, the
Hongkong Bank,
has now engaged Lowe Bell Communications to fight its corner.
Once upon a time GJW and Lowe Bell were all part of the same Frank Lowe
media empire. And although Sir Tim Bell, Mrs Thatcher's favourite spin
doctor, has bought out Lowe Bell, Lowe Group still retains a 20 per cent
stake and so benefits both ways.
Nevertheless, one wonders what happened to that no-
compete clause whereby GJW and Lowe Bell are supposed to work together
rather than against each other. This is the first time that Sir Tim has
challenged his old partners.
</TEXT>
