FT  06 MAY 92 / Mujahideen named as Afghan ministers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Foreign Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE new Islamic government of Afghanistan named 36 mujahideen leaders as
ministers in the transitional administration that took power a week ago, as
a barrage of rockets killed at least 40 people and wounded 200, Our Foreign
Staff writes.
Dozens of rockets fired by fighters supporting Mr Gulbuddin Hekmatyar landed
throughout the city after government forces began an offensive at first
light.
Apart from Mr Ahmad Shah Masood, who was named defence minister before the
government formally took power, and Mr Ahmad Shah, the interior minister,
all the ministers were appointed for only two months.
