FT  05 MAY 92 / UK Company News: O&amp;Y to reveal asset sales this week
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
OLYMPIA &amp; York Developments, the beleaguered international developer, said
it plans to announce the sale of assets later this week as part of its debt
restructuring programme, AP-DJ reports from Toronto.
The company said it continues to seek additional cash from its bankers as
part of the restructuring. 'O&amp;Y also is pursuing other alternatives to
address its liquidity problems, including the sale of assets, some of which
will be announced later this week,' the company said. An O&amp;Y spokesman
declined to elaborate.
The company also said it missed making an interest payment of about CDollars
17m (USDollars 14.2m) due yesterday. The payment was to be made to holders
of its Series 1 and 2 bonds, secured by its First Canadian Place office
tower in Toronto. The bonds have a principal value of CDollars 325m.
